{
  "slug": "resist-decoration-wax-emulsion-on-clay",
  "title": "Wax-emulsion resist decoration on air-dry clay",
  "subtitle": "Using a wax resist to mask areas before applying a slip wash",
  "excerpt": "Wax emulsion brushed onto dry air-dry clay forms a water-resistant mask. A coloured slip or diluted acrylic wash applied over the top pools in the unmasked areas but beads off the waxed sections, creating a two-tone patterned surface. No kiln required.",
  "type": "TECHNIQUE",
